Options: {'A': 'Bipolar disorder, manic, with psychotic features', 'B': 'Brief psychotic disorder', 'C': 'Delusional disorder', 'D': 'Psychotic disorder due to general medical condition', 'E': 'Schizophrenia'}

A 62-year-old woman with myasthenia gravis comes to the office because of a 2-week history of falling.
